    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.6: \"GR and MR labeling at asymmetrical synapses\"\n- \"MR-ir and GR-ir was expressed in pre- and postsynaptic sites. Qualitative examination of asymmetrical synapses revealed both GR-ir and MR-ir (MA1-620 and rMR1-18 1D5) at the PSD (Fig. 6B-D) and MR-ir at the presynaptic terminal (Fig. 6D), compared to the primary antibody omitted PSD (Fig. 6A).\"\n\nFig.7: \"Quantitative analysis of labeling at postsynaptic density of asymmetrical synapses\"\n- \"Planned contrasts between the groups revealed a significant difference between the primary antibody omitted control and both MRs and GR (t=10.496; p<.001).\". Experimental description: \"20 male Sprague-Dawley rats with intact adrenal glands were used in this study\"",
